#SimplePracties #VoiceofHope

To ensure children learn meaningfully inside classrooms, our educators are adopting the simple practice of "Recall" 🔁

A visual recall of  from the previous classroom, solidifies their learnings from the class and enables children to build continuity in future classrooms. This simple practice is helping our educators and children strengthen learning despite a post-covid slide in attention span! 

⬇️Watch this video to see how Prerna ma'am, an educator from one of our Centres of Excellence (MCD Primary Government School, Bhim Nagri) used a video recall with her children to enable them to go back to the concept of grouping. 

📣We invite educators and non-educators in our community to share practices you use with children to tackle 
this challenge! Let us know in the comments!

#learning #teachersarenationbuilders #highquality #practices #covid #recall #studentlearning #governmentschools

At SEF, we always say, "it takes time to make change", the journey of school transformation is a beautiful testament to that.

From the day you step into a school, change slowly unfolds in front of you and last month as we saw the first batch of students from our earliest school transformation program graduate from Grade 5, we took a moment to pause and savour all the small and big changes we witnessed over the past 5 years! 💛

And we made sure the day was marked with happiness and pride of parents, teachers and our children 🙌🎉

Big shout out to everyone who has played a role in this journey!

We are entering this new year, with new learnings and hopes to see more of our children graduate and reach new heights. Watch this space to see what enabled us to bring to live our vision of transformation!

#schooltransformation #students #growth #teachers #nationbuilders #reinventinggovernmentschools #happiness #celebrations #newacademicyear

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
We asked people what is the one word they would use to describe a teacher?

And it is clear that the work that they do goes beyond the walls of schools and impacts our lives in meaningful ways. 

This Teachers’ Day we want to say #Shukriya to all teachers.💐

Shukriya for being a life saver, 
Shukriya for being a mentor,
Shukriya for being a symbol of love and hope. 
And, Shukriya for your service in leading this nation down a better path. 

Join us in expressing our #shukr.

latestIgtvVideos.title: What do you think children need today?
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
The COVID-19 Pandemic has exposed children to a sudden shift to online learning. Children find themselves isolated and vulnerable in these spaces but by taking small steps we can ensure this experience is worthwhile for them.

We asked a few people “In today's day of online learning, what is the support every child should have and from whom?” - Children need to be heard and they need to know that you care, are some of the responses we received.

Let us know what you think children need, in the comments below!

#TakeTheFirstStep #NoCurfewForEducation #EducationForAll #QualityLearning

latestPosts.caption:
“What brings people to SEF?

For some, it’s the chance to reimagine education. For others, it’s the culture of care, collaboration, and deep purpose. 💛
At SEF, we’re not just building better classrooms — we’re building a better India, together.

✨ When teachers thrive, children flourish. When children flourish, India prospers. 

👉🏽 Tap to hear their stories.
#WhySEF #PeopleOfSEF #TeamSEF #PurposeInAction #EducationForAll #VoicesFromTheField

Behind every thriving individual, there is a great teacher.
But have you ever paused to ask — who is behind that teacher? 🤔

At Simple Education Foundation (SEF), we believe that every teacher deserves the same care, trust, and opportunity 🌱 that we expect them to offer their students.

We work with teachers in government schools — not just to improve teaching techniques 📚, but to restore purpose and joy in teaching ✨.
Because a teacher who feels seen, supported, and valued becomes unstoppable 💪🏼.

And when teachers thrive, children flourish 🌼 — and when children flourish, India prospers 🇮🇳.

This is how SEF is transforming public education — one teacher at a time, one classroom at a time.🏫❤️

#TeachersOfIndia #TeacherTraining #TeachingThatMatters #teachersfortomorrow #simpleeducationfoundation #empowerindia

When purpose meets people. 💛

Teams from Delhi, Uttarakhand, and Punjab came together to reconnect with SEF’s vision and mission, welcome new team members, and celebrate each other’s work through powerful learning showcases.

The induction wrapped up with reflective facilitation sessions that brought clarity, collaboration, and fresh energy to kickstart the year.

All of us — from different geographies, backgrounds, and roles — united by one dream: to make excellent education accessible to every child.

👉🏽 Tap to see how we grow together — and stay tuned for more stories of purpose, people, and progress.

#TeamSEF #Induction2025 #TogetherWeGrow

Think of a time when you asked a child who they want to be when they grow up.

Their eyes light up — with dreams, with hope, with no limitations🌈

Children dream big, by default.

And it is our responsibility — as adults, caregivers, and educators — to build a world where those dreams can come true. To act today, to not give up.🎉

That’s why SEF works to improve life and learning outcomes in government schools — by ensuring every child has access to an excellent teacher.

✨ 3 Days of Learning, Laughter & Literacy! ✨
Our team had the incredible opportunity to lead a 3-day training under the NIPUN Sankalp Programme at SCERT Delhi, working with passionate primary teacher trainers from across the city.

The trainers are now ready to take the trainings to thousands of teachers across Delhi! 

Together, we explored actionable strategies and tools to introduce Foundational Literacy and Numeracy (FLN-Math's and Hindi) in classrooms — from playful techniques to powerful tools that make learning stick.

Because when learning is fun, children thrive. 🌱📚

👉 Know a teacher who'd love to make learning joyful? Tag them below or share this with your network!
Let’s reimagine classrooms, one joyful lesson at a time. 💫

When teachers see beyond behaviour and respond with empathy, children feel safe to learn, explore, and thrive.

latestPosts.caption:
Are we truly preparing our teachers for the classrooms they face today?

In our recent webinar “Understanding Teacher Professional Development @ Scale”, panelists Siddesh Sarma (Leadership For Equity), Gayatri Vaidya (Educational Initiatives), and Chandni Chopra (Simple Education Foundation) shared honest, experience-rich insights from years of working in schools and systems.

They explored critical questions we often overlook:
👉 Why do teachers feel disconnected from most trainings?
👉 How do we design for real classroom contexts, like multi-grade, multi-level teaching?
👉 Can training go beyond content delivery to shift classroom practice and student outcomes?

The conversation unpacked both the persistent challenges and promising pathways forward, from using assessments to personalize TPD, to building strong mentoring systems, and designing training that centers teacher voice and child outcomes.

Whether you are a policymaker, school leader, practitioner, or education advocate, this discussion is packed with practical takeaways and bold ideas to rethink how we support our teachers.

Click the link in the bio to watch the full webinar and dive into a conversation that’s shaping the future of teacher development in India.

#TeacherTraining #ProfessionalDevelopment #ScalingEducation #EducationReform #LFE #EI #SEF #TeachersMatter #TransformingEducation

“For children to truly thrive, we must see them fully — their contexts, their challenges, and their potential. 🌱

In this reflection, Srinidhi Lakshmanan reminds us that systems and people must work together to meet children where they are.

At Simple Education Foundation, we equip teachers in government schools to create classrooms where children’s needs are the centre. Where they feel safe, seen, and supported to shape their future!

Learn more about our work here- https://lnkd.in/dMTM9NK5

Have you watched SEF’s latest film yet? 

If not, now’s the time—watch it and witness what’s possible when we reimagine public education together.

High up in the hills of Uttarakhand and deep within the lanes of Delhi, something quiet—but deeply powerful—is taking shape in #Government schools.

In 7 schools across these geographies, we’ve been holding onto one transformative question:

➡️What does it truly take for every child in a Government school to thrive?

For the past 3+ years, we’ve partnered closely with teachers—co-creating schools where learning is joyful, teaching is meaningful, and change is real.

They’re living models of transformation—growing, evolving, and built to be shared.

At SEF, we equip teachers with skills and mindsets, needed to prepare every child for their future. This future begins in schools.

📽️ Watch the film now (link in bio)

#educationforall #sef #transformingeducation #simpleeducationfoundation

“At SEF, our approach has always been simple: listen closely to what’s working — in a single classroom, in a cluster of schools — and build systems that scale with integrity and effectiveness” – Shrutika Silswal, Head of Uttarakhand Programs at SEF

In this month’s edition of #SimplerTimes, Shrutika takes us on a short memory trip through our journey in Uttarakhand — highlighting how deep partnerships with the government have enabled change at scale.

As SEF grows, our commitment remains rooted in designing solutions that are relevant to teachers and responsive to children’s needs. Our journey in Uttarakhand is a powerful testament to the importance of scaling with depth.

#education #Governmentschools #learning #program
